BBC on Wednesday announced a new scheme for journalists with disabilities in Kenya, titled "Aim High". The new scheme was announced by BBC director general Tony Hall, who was in attendance. "The new initiative will offer three-month placements to three aspiring journalists with disabilities, starting from April 2020," he said. In attendance were BBC British Chamber of Commerce's Graham Shaw, head of East Africa language Rachel Okwir and Star head of content Paul Ilado. The event took place at Serena Hotel, Nairobi.